# GCP Guidance

## Project Context

- GCP target: {{ gcp_target | default("Cloud Run, Cloud Build, or detected service") }}
- Config files: {{ gcp_config_files | default("app.yaml, cloudbuild.yaml, or project config") }}
- Containerized: {{ uses_docker | default("detected by Akira") }}

## Configuration

- Keep project IDs, regions, and service names configurable.
- Use service accounts with least privilege.
- Store secrets in Secret Manager or the platform's configured secret channel.
- Keep deployment config reviewable in source control without secret values.
- Keep IAM changes separate enough to review permissions clearly.
- Prefer workload identity or platform-provided credentials over service account
  key files.

## Runtime

- Read environment variables at application startup or settings boundaries.
- Make health checks cheap and dependency-aware.
- Emit logs to stdout/stderr in a format Cloud Logging can ingest.
- Keep request timeouts and concurrency aligned with the service's workload.
- Make startup failures explicit so unhealthy revisions do not receive traffic.
- Keep local emulator usage behind configuration flags when applicable.

